fix: stale async chain + steps=0 via runId session cancellation

Root cause: stopSession() does not cancel in-flight runKeyword() calls.
When a second START arrives during ATTACHING, stopSession() runs but
the first runKeyword() continues executing asynchronously, calling
setState("SCRAPING") concurrently with the new session's setState("ATTACHING").
This caused FSM collision: SCRAPING->ATTACHING, and cdpScrollEngine's
while(S.state==="SCRAPING") exited immediately -> steps=0.

Fix: added S.runId counter (integer, incremented on each session start
and on stopSession). All async chains capture runId at entry and abort
if S.runId changes before they reach a key checkpoint:
- runKeyword(sid): aborts if S.runId !== sid before SCRAPING
- cdpScrollEngine(kw, sid): while loop condition includes S.runId===sid
- finalizeKeyword(sid): skips reconcile if S.runId !== sid
- runKeyword recursive call: checks S.runId===sid before next keyword
- stopSession: S.runId++ + S.scrollRunning=false to release all locks
